#1954
Initiatory chamber~
This chamber seems to be where new members to the cult are initiated.  A
variety of sinister-looking devices are arranged around the walls, while a
large shallow pool of steaming water stands in the center.  A massive iconic
portrait of a charismatic-looking man dominates the western wall, and
underneath is some writing.  
~
~
1 11
E
devices~
The devices are similar to those you'd expect to see in a torture
chamber, but here they are used to "purify" the body and soul of the
initiate.  
~
E
pool~
The water in the pool is bubbling and steaming up from a
mineral-encrusted hole at the center.  Clearly this is fed by some kind of
natural hot spring.  
~
E
portrait~
The artist who painted this portrait was either mad or a genius, probably
both.  He has captured something about the face and eyes that makes them
strangely compelling, and you find it difficult to look away.  
~
